  "prompt": "How can I see the saved Wi-Fi passwords on my mobile?",
  "response": "The method to view saved Wi-Fi passwords depends on your mobile device's operating system:\n\nFor Android:\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Select \"Wi-Fi\" or \"Connections\"\n3. Tap the saved network\n4. Select \"Share\" or \"QR code\"\n5. You may need to use your device's screen lock authentication\n\nAlternative Android method:\n1. Go to Settings\n2. Select \"Wi-Fi\"\n3. Tap the gear/settings icon next to the network\n4. Select \"Modify network\"\n5. Check \"Show password\"\n\nFor iPhone:\n1. You'll need to sync with a Mac computer\n2. Open Keychain Access\n3. Search for the Wi-Fi network name\n4. Check the password\n\nRooted Android/Jailbroken iPhone:\n1. Use third-party apps like Wi-Fi Password Viewer\n2. These require advanced device permissions\n\nNote: Some methods might require:\n- Administrator/root access\n- Screen lock authentication\n- Latest device software\n\nAlways ensure you have permission before accessing network passwords.",
